### Medium Severity

#### 5. Eager Test — `OrderProcessor_FullWorkflow_Succeeds`

```csharp
processor.ValidateOrder(order);
processor.CalculateTotal(order);
processor.ApplyDiscount(order, "SAVE10");
processor.ReserveInventory(order);
processor.ProcessPayment(order, new CreditCard("4111111111111111"));
processor.SendConfirmation(order);
processor.UpdateOrderHistory(order);
Assert.AreEqual("Completed", order.Status);
```

**Risk:** 7 distinct production methods called. When this test fails, you have no idea which step broke. Each method deserves its own focused test. The single assertion at the end only checks the final status, not the intermediate effects.

**Fix:** If you need an integration/workflow test, keep it but name it explicitly as such. Then add focused unit tests for each method individually:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void ApplyDiscount_ValidCode_ReducesTotal()
{
    // ... test ApplyDiscount in isolation
}

[TestMethod]
public void ReserveInventory_SufficientStock_ReservesItems()
{
    // ... test ReserveInventory in isolation
}
```

