### Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Fix | Effort |
|----------|-------|-----|--------|
| 1 | Assertion-Free Test | Add assertions | 5 min |
| 2 | Conditional Test Logic | Split into two tests | 10 min |
| 3 | Sleepy Test | Switch to async/await | 15 min |
| 4 | Mystery Guest | Inline test data | 5 min |
| 5 | Exception Handling | Use `Assert.ThrowsException` | 5 min |
| 6 | Magic Numbers | Extract named constants + messages | 10 min |
| 7 | Sensitive Equality | Assert on properties | 5 min |
| 8 | Eager Test | Extract focused unit tests | 20 min |
| 9 | General Fixture | Remove unused `_logger` | 1 min |

Priorities 1–4 are the most impactful — they address tests that can silently pass while the code is broken, or that fail non-deterministically in CI.
